ALLADI VENKATESWARLU & ORS V. GOVT. OF ANDHRA PRADESH & ANR [1978] INSC 46; AIR 1978 SC 945; 1978 (2) SCR 190; 1978 (2) SCC 552 (21 February 1978)

 BEG, M. HAMEEDULLAH (CJ) BEG, M. HAMEEDULLAH (CJ) UNTWALIA, N.L.
 
CITATION: 1978 AIR 945 1978 SCR (2) 190 1978 SCC (2) 552 
ACT:
 Interpretation of taxing statute--If the language is clear, it will be unfair to interpret against the assessee.
 Andhra Pradesh General Sales Tax Act, 1957 S. 5 r/w Entry 66 of Schedule I to the Act--When "Paddy" was already taxed under item 8 Schedule II, Whether "Atukulu" (Parched Rice) and "muramuralu" (Puffed rice) are exigible to tax for the second time as rice falling under Item 66(a) of Schedule I--Whether "Atukulu" (Parched rice) and "muramuralu" (Puffed rice) are "rice" within the meaning of entry 66(b) of Schedule I.
 Andhra Pradesh General Sales Tax Act, 1957, Section 5(2)--Difference between taxation u/s 5(2)(a) and 5(2)(b).
 
